September 12 at 1:00 PM ¬∑

Please join us in welcoming him!

post_text:
Coronavirus Food Assistance Program SUSPENDED

The Coronavirus Food Assistance Program, which allowed the district to provide supplemental food boxes to our families, has been suspended immediately due to an expiration of federal funding. This will not affect the regular food distribution service that provides grab-and-go student lunches.

We are sorry for any inconvenience as we understand that the supplemental program benefited many in our community. Should the program restart, we will be sure to share the new distribution information.

post_text: At last Monday‚Äôs board of education meeting, FVPD President Chuck Anderson and Vice President Matt Hicks Jr. presented West Aurora School District 129 with a check for $250,000. The money will be used towards building a new, accessible playground for the students of Hope D. Wall School and for children of all abilities in the Aurora area. The old wooden playscape, which was built in 1993, has been torn down and the construction of the new playground has begun this week!

TODAY!

August 25 from 4-5pm CST, join ADA 25 Leadership for an exclusive briefing on the importance of people with disabilities being counted in the 2020 Census. People with disabilities are an intersectional cross-identity group and are one of the largest minority populations and counting. People with disabilities deserve to be counted in the 2020 Census inclusive of race/ethnicity, citizenship, age, or legal status as their lives depend on it. The ongoing COVID-19 pandemic has only underscored the need for a complete and accurate count for all.

Attendees of the webinar will hear from Census officials and community members who will share their updates and perspectives on the current 2020 Census count and how you can use your power to ensure a complete count this year.

Power and Justice: A 2020 Census Conversation
08/25/2020 04:00 PM - 05:00 PM CST
https://ada25chicago.z2systems.com/np/clients/ada25chicago/event.jsp?event=69&

West Aurora Challenge Coin üî¥üîµ

Three lifelong supporters of the West Aurora schools have been awarded West Aurora Challenge Coins by Superintendent of Schools, Dr. Jeff Craig. These recipients have dedicated years of service for our students, schools, and community. They are the epitome of a West Aurora Blackhawk!

Challenge coins, which began as a military tradition, have become a widely recognized way of showing membership and boosting morale. West Aurora has minted a limited number of coins that will be presented to those leaders in the West Aurora School District and community who personify commitment, courage, excellence, and integrity.

West Aurora Families,

Want to know what your student‚Äôs schedule will look like during virtual learning?

Please take a moment to view the bell schedules for middle & high school as well as a sample schedule for elementary.

Reminder:
Synchronous learning is learning that happens at the same time for the instructor and the learners, meaning that there's real-time interaction between them. Asynchronous learning applies to tasks that students complete on their own (or in small groups), which is not being delivered by the teacher in real-time.

High School: https://documentcloud.adobe.com/link/track?uri=urn:aaid:scds:US:38eeb3ac-6588-440c-b427-b49742afccc8

Middle School:https://documentcloud.adobe.com/link/track?uri=urn:aaid:scds:US:913630af-5a3f-4a5b-9650-67fba975b50e

Elementary School Sample: https://documentcloud.adobe.com/link/track?uri=urn:aaid:scds:US:86ca83e3-2e86-4f2d-889d-51e2081fe975

Questions? Please email questions@sd129.org to get your question answered in our FAQ section under https://www.sd129.org/20-21-reopening-plan

post_text:
West Aurora High School is pleased to announce the success of its six FCCLA National Delegates!

Earlier this summer, our delegates submitted their STAR event projects which were then evaluated remotely by judges from across the country. Later in July, club sponsors Linda Nudera and Katey Armstrong hosted a safe, "socially distant" viewing party during the organization's first-ever virtual National Leadership Conference. Not only were the students able to engage in virtual demonstrations and learn about possible career opportunities, but they also received national recognition for their work! West Aurora is proud of the following Blackhawks for reaching their goal of competing at a national level with their career-related projects:

DASHA CHAVEZ - Fashion Construction - Silver - 27th Nationally
EMILY HEAD & JAZMIN JUAREZ - Interior Design - Gold - 6th Nationally
REGAN MEHLBRECH - Leadership - Silver - 8th Nationally
ABBIGAIL ROE - Professional Presentation - Silver - 21st Nationally
YAMAYRA VILLA - Entrepreneurship - Silver - 25th Nationally

West Aurora Graduates,

To request a copy of your final transcript, please email anunez@sd129.org. In that communication, please include:
-Your name
-Your ID number
-The destination information where the transcript is going
-The number of copies

Additionally:
-Requested transcripts will be sent in the last week of June.
-If you have already requested your transcript through Naviance, you do not need to do anything further.
-Any transcript requests made on or after August 1st need to be made through Parchment.com. (Do not use Parchment.com prior to August 1st.)
-All fees have to be paid and any school-issued materials need to be turned in before a transcript can be released. (ie Chromebooks/chargers)

Dear School District 129 Families,

In collaboration with the City of Aurora and local authorities, all District 129 facilities will be reopening starting tomorrow, Wednesday, June 3rd. This means:

-All seven of our food distribution centers will again be available Monday through Friday, 10 am to 1 pm, through August 7th.

-The collection of materials by staff and students will resume. Please see communication from individual schools regarding these processes.

-The new hours of operation for all district buildings will be 8 am to 3 pm, Monday through Thursday, by appointment only.

Thank you for your continued support of School District 129.

Sincerely,
Jeff Craig, Ed.D.
Superintendent
West Aurora School District 129

West Aurora Families,

Due to construction work, the food distribution process will look slightly different at two of our buildings this week:

-At West Aurora High School, please use door 18 (off of Commonwealth, near the auditorium) on Tuesday, May 19th.

Pettyjohn, MSgt. Scott Hellinger, SMSgt. Matthew Pierzchala, and our cadets for this incredible accomplishment!

post_text:
Making Kane Fit For Kids aims to promote healthy eating and active living initiatives to reduce childhood obesity in Kane County.

Recently, West Aurora applied for their grant and was awarded the resources to purchase nine exercise bicycles for Washington Middle School's fitness room!

The benefit of additional equipment increases the amount of time a student in PE can reach a peak heart rate during the class period. This is the third district project supported by the Fit for Kids initiative! West Aurora thanks Fit for Kids for their continued partnership!

post_text: Support our local businesses! There are still meaningful ways to celebrate the milestones of spring with family by enjoying a meal safely at home. Blackhawks, give Mom a day off for Mothers Day and let someone else cook!
shared_text:
AURORADOWNTOWN.ORG
Aurora Downtown's "Carry Out Days" offers weekly specials in May ¬ª Aurora Downtown | SSA #One | Aurora, Ill

Gillerson's Grubbery is feeling grateful.
May 5 at 3:24 PM ¬∑

Gillerson‚Äôs Grubbery was started in 2015 with the hopes of being a staple in Downtown Aurora for years to come! It‚Äôs 5 years later and now more than ever we need all of our customers to continue to support us! The amount of orders over the past month have warned our hearts, especially those meals for Essential Workers! It shows how much you all love our community!

As much as we love our customers, our staff have been working their butts off before and during this shutdown. The same 10ish people have been working this entire time and have made the best of this weird situation.

So really what we‚Äôre trying to say is THANK YOU TO OUR AMAZING STAFF AND DEDICATED CUSTOMERS!

Please continue to support local small businesses so we can all return to whatever normal will be when we can reopen our dining room to you!

post_text:
HOSA State Leadership Conference VICTORIES!

The 2020 Illinois HOSA State Leadership Conference was to be held in Springfield in late March. Due to the COVID-19 crisis, the onsite event was canceled and a virtual version of the conference was established. Over the course of three weeks, our HOSA competitors took tests, submitted portfolios, and recorded videos to be reviewed by judges.

The results are in! Congratulations to all of the HOSA students and their efforts during the first-ever Virtual State Leadership Conference!

WAHS TOTALS:
53 State Finalists (ranked in the top ten)
7 National Qualifiers (ranked in the top 3)
2 State Champions
6 State officers, including President of Illinois HOSA
1 Scholarship Winner
1 Outstanding State Leader

post_text:
West Aurora High School students continue to impress!

The Seal of Biliteracy Program recognizes high school students who have attained a high level of proficiency in one or more languages in addition to English. Two honors are available: the Seal of Biliteracy and the Commendation toward Biliteracy.

This year, a total of 168 total awards were earned by the Class of 2020, with 100 students receiving the Seal of Biliteracy and 68 students earning the Commendation toward Biliteracy. 10 students also earned seals in two languages!

Keep working hard, Blackhawks. We are proud of you!

The Aurora Community Alliance Presents: The Ask Event

The Aurora Community Alliance (ACA), a monthly meeting of community partners that come together; with the goal of providing education and reducing drug use among youth in our community.

This virtual event is an opportunity for students, parents, and community members to ask any questions they have regarding mental health, drug use, legal consequences, and more; and hear specific answers from expert panelists.

From the SD129, Honor House Social Worker, Michelle Voris, will be a panelist to represent West High.

If you have any questions you would like to submit please follow this link: https://bit.ly/3f6dfv0

The Aurora Community Alliance Presents: The Ask Event

The Aurora Community Alliance (ACA), a monthly meeting of community partners that come together; with the goal of providing education and reducing drug use among youth in our community.

This virtual event is an opportunity for students, parents, and community members to ask any questions they have regarding mental health, drug use, legal consequences, and more; and hear specific answers from expert panelists.

From the SD129, Honor House Social Worker, Michelle Voris, will be a panelist to represent West High.

District 129 Parents/Guardians:
Although our schools and offices are closed during this challenging time, we ask that you please enroll your student for the 2020-2021 school year by following the button below. We are still honoring your home school enrollment guarantee if you log in and register on or before May 1st.
https://www.sd129.org/district/departments/operations/admissions

For assistance with logging into your Home Access account, password reset, or questions about the enrollment form itself, please contact PowerSchool Support at 866-434-6276.

For support and questions about District 129 required documentation or address changes, please contact the admissions office at 630-301-5050 or registration@sd129.org. Although phones will go directly to voicemail, please leave a detailed message and someone will return your call as quickly as possible.
